neighborhood_overview: Be right in the heart of the Golden Square… el Quadrat d’Or! As if it were an open-air museum, the Eixample's Golden Square embraces the most important modernist architectural works: Casa Batlló, La Pedrera and Casa Amatller. Some of the most valued buildings of the city designed by the best architects of a golden age that still remain alive in the memory of its streets. The Golden Square is bordered by Carrer Aribau and Passeig de Sant Joan, by Avinguda Diagonal at the top and Plaça de Catalunya at the bottom, its main artery is the famous Passeig de Gràcia, an avenue of leisure that became extremely glamorous in Barcelona: 1.5km of luxury shops, culture, good food, mediterranean lifestyle and its gems of modernist architecture. ["We had the whole apartment to ourselves and really enjoyed it. The kitchen was well-equipped and the flat was super cozy and nicely decorated. Leonor is a really friendly host, we'd definitely come back here!", "Leo's apartment is in a great location, right next to the Triumphal Arch metro station. You can walk with kids to Sagrada Familia, Plaza Catalonia, Rambla, zoo, and even the French train station for trips to Port Aventura.

The apartment itself is small, but the living room and bedroom windows face the street, which can be noisy at night. The other two bedrooms have windows that look into the hallway. 

Leo is a nice lady, and there's everything you need in the building for life and food. There's tons of dishes. 

The only downside is the neighbor downstairs who doesn't like any noise. Leo warned us about him when we arrived, but he started complaining about the noisy stairs that day. We realized how serious it was when he went to complain about the noise. The kids were scared and constantly had to be told to be quiet, and he kept coming to our door.  We never made a big deal of it, just kids running around and laughing loudly, and then he starts banging on the door. This is stressful during vacation. 

Not recommended for families with kids. Great for adults.", "Leonor has a great apartment right next to the Arc de Triumph. It's only a 10-minute walk to Catalunya Square. name: 2633 - AB Barceloneta - Artistic Style Apartment - Beachside apartment for 2 with balcony and WiFi
summary: This contemporary apartment is located in the Barceloneta district, just steps away from the beach and the Mediterranean Sea, offering a balcony, air conditioning and free Wi-Fi. Parc de la Ciutadella and the Arc de Triomf are just over 15 minutes’ walk away, and the city’s picturesque  Old Town is under 1km away where you can find the Picasso Museum, the Basilica de Santa Maria del Mar and the Palau de la Música Catalana. Barceloneta metro station is just 700 metres away.   The apartment accommodates 2 people, containing 1 double bed. The kitchen is equipped with a microwave, hob cooker and large fridge freezer. The apartment also contains a washing machine, flatscreen TV, and central heating.  Within a short walk you will find plenty of museums, restaurants, bars and shops. summary: Confortable, hogareño y funcional estudio en edificio completamente rehabilitado. Localizado en el distinguido barrio Eixample derecho de Barcelona, donde se encuentran los lugares más emblemáticos de la ciudad.
space: Este moderno y equipado estudio está diseñado para garantizar una estancia cómoda y confortable. Se accede por el hall de entrada, encontrándose justo a un lado, el walk-in closet. Seguidamente se accede a un espacio abierto donde encontramos el dormitorio que se halla separado del resto del estudio por una pared que linda con la cocina. La cama doble del dormitorio puede dividirse en dos camas individuales de 90cm x 200cm y dispone de mesitas de noche con luz e iluminación de lectura. Tras el dormitorio se encuentra el espacio general comprendido por la cocina integrada y la sala, donde podremos cocinar, leer, mirar TV o relajarse en el gran sofá que se halla en la sala. Este sofá puede convertirse en cama doble alojando así 2 huéspedes más. El baño presenta una ducha a nivel del suelo con divisoria de vidrio templado y dispone de cómodos sanitarios, además de espejo y dos cajoneras. Todas las ventanas disponen de doble cortina para oscurecer el ambiente o dejar que pase la luz natura

The apartment is just a 2-minute walk from the Museu d’Art Contemporani de Barcelona, also known as MACBA, and a 12-minute walk from the famous Las Ramblas. Plaça de Catalunya, the most central point of Barcelona, is also less than a 10-minute walk from the apartment.  Within a short walk, you will find plenty of museums, restaurants, bars, cafés and shops. This neighbourhood is a great choice for those interested in the local culture and being in the heart of the city.Metro: Universitat (L1, L2) & Sant Antoni (L2)

Les photos ne correspondent plus à 100% (j'en ai prise sur place)
Chambre : petite, pas de place prévue pour mettre son linge, le lit n'est pas très confortable (les ressorts font mal au dos), pas de Wi-Fi, 2 malheureuses chaines de télévision, fils de la TV qui pendent du mur, mur sale, tapis de sol sale, oreillers qui sentent mauvais, serviettes rêches et malodorantes .
Ventilateur capricieux, ne fonctionne que par intermittence. Lorsque l'on laisse la fenêtre ouverte, impossible de dormir à cause du bruit...
Terrasse communique avec la chambre d'à côté, difficile donc de la laisser ouverte en journée.
Salles de bain : les diffuseurs multi-jets des 2 salles de bain sont plein de calcaire, le fil de douche rouille,  tapis de sol sale, sol d'une des 2 douches sale, W-C peu nettoyés et pas très propres. une des 2 cabines de douche est trop petite et la paroi vitrée de la seconde douche n'a pas été nettoyé une seule fois en 8 jours, chasse d'eau d'un des 2 W-C met 8 minutes à se remplir (pas très pratique)
Cuisine : essuies sales, vaisselle de la "cousine" qui n'est faite que le lendemain de l'utilisation (24 heures après), frigo pas propre.
Il manque une table pour pouvoir manger à son aise.
Salon : canapé plein de taches, le mur n'est pas celui de la photo car il est tout blanc, coussins sales, TV multi-chaînes.
Balcon arrière : petit, il y a une machine à laver et le linge personnel de "la cousine" qui sèche toute la journée, donc pour le petit déjeuner en terrasse c'est raté.
Toit aménagé : dégueulasse, vieux frigo, bbq, vieux sofas de plage et autres qui traînent. L'endroit ne donne pas envie de s'y attarder.
Situation : quartier vraiment sympa et situation géographique intéressante pour visiter la ville.
Divers : on sonne à toute heure pour les arrivées, ce qui est normal... mais la cousine n'entend pas cela à cause de sa musique ou du fait qu'elle dort et l'insistance de la sonnette devient dès lors embêtant.
"La cousine " (désolé, j'ai oublié son prénom) est sympa et donne des conseils touristiques si nécessaire.
Le commentaire est chargé et négatif mais je l'estime sincère .
C'était ma première expérience en Bnb et je crains que ce sera la dernière.
J'estime que cela ne vaut absolument pas son prix et je regrette de ne pas avoir réserver un hôtel car la différence de prix n'est pas si énorme.
Bref, je regrette cette malheureuse expérience et c'est moche lorsque l'on s'offre une semaine.
Je regrette mais je ne recommande vraiment pas l'endroit.

["My friend and I were happy we could book this place instantly. We booked it the night before and it fit our needs. We got a nice tour when we arrived. There were tons of pamphlets with info on things to do in Barcelona.  We found a bike tour there that we wouldn't have found otherwise - that was the best part of our trip! Wifi worked best in the living room, not so good in our room. The kitchen area was nice. We didn't use it much because we only stayed one night. Other people were staying here too, so it was a little loud but not bad at all. Our bed was comfy. The people who run this place live downstairs if you need anything, which is great. Thanks for the awesome place to stay in Barcelona for one night!", 'It was a great spot, and the house had all the stuff we needed!', 'More like a hostel than an apartment, but it was okay. The bed was comfy and there were no problems.', "Awesome place, the hosts were super nice (even picked me up from the airport!).  Clean and comfy. The apartment is right by everything you'd want to check out. I'd definitely stay here again!", 'Monique's cousin gave us a pretty cold welcome. She explained everything to us, but in a way that wasn't exactly welcoming, but not unfriendly either. At the end of our stay we asked if we could leave our luggage there because we were leaving in the evening and it was no problem, which was nice. 

The neighborhood is okay - things aren't within walking distance (for example to the Ramblas it's about 1.5 km), but you can get everywhere with the subway. The Poble Sec station is around the corner, a bit less than 5 minutes walk. 

The room itself was alright, it was spacious and bright, but there were some flaws. For example there are no closets or bedside tables. So in the few days we were there all our clothes that we unpacked (we traveled with backpacks) laid either on the bed or on the makeshift "wardrobe" (which is more or less a hallstand with a little space where the extra blanket was). A real problem to fix. Minor issue: I had trouble locking up the door. About the other rooms: the bathrooms were pretty dirty, the shower, as well as the faucet and mirror. The bathroom size is nice and there's no problem getting along with the other guests because there are two. Kitchen: we didn't use it much, but it was fine, everything you needed was there. 

The apartment overall was okay, but nothing more and not worth the price, sorry.', 'A really cozy place, super clean and in a great location. Monique is a good host.', "Since this is our first time in Barcelona, we were a little worried about our stay. Monique's brother, Ignor, gave us a shuttle from the airport to our house for 25 euros. Ignor picked us up at the airport and since it was too early to check in (9 AM), he took us to a cafe nearby. He treated us to breakfast and we really appreciate it. Ignor warned us about pickpockets and told us about places of interest, entertainment spots, and our surroundings. He made us feel very comfortable in Barcelona. He's been a big help!

The room was okay. Simple and good enough for travelers. The train station was about 15 minutes away. The neighborhood was pretty safe. I would recommend this place to other travelers.", 'The place is great, you can see a nice view from the windows. name: Bright, Central Apartment with Traditional and Modern Design
summary: Experience Barcelona's bohemian side at this traditional flat with a modern twist. This spacious retreat has traditional tile floors, a Catalan vault ceiling, and repointed brick. Features a fully-equipped kitchen and balcony overlooking the street. The apartment is located near Ramblas.
space: This apartment offers 2 double rooms and a private bathroom for guests. I share my home with my guests, this is not a full apartment reservation. The kitchen, equipped with all necessary gears and utensils, features a nice open plan on which to enjoy a drink or a dinner. The apartment has heating system in all rooms as well as air conditioning in the living room but bedrooms have only fans. This central 75m2 apartment is strategically located near Ramblas and the port of Barcelona. The neighbourhood is safe and vibrant with many bars, restaurants and many opportunities to enjoy the city. A unique place to be for a fantastic Barcelona experience, surrounded by everything you need to know, visit and taste.

neighborhood_overview: El Raval offers a central location within walking distance of many of the other popular areas—such as the Gothic Quarter and Eixample—and many of the city's main attractions.
notes: You have all flexibility to move in the apartment, you can use the balcony for smoking and enjoy just the vibe over the street.  If you feel like a home-cooked meal, the gorgeous remodeled kitchen comes fully equipped with all the appliances and gadgets. The living room area enjoys the rustic original ceilings and patterned tiles that give the property its cozy feeling. We offer you the following: - High speed Wifi at 300Mb/s; ⁃ The new modern kitchen has all brand new appliances such as fridge; oven, cooker, kettle along with cooking utensils, pots, pans and more; ⁃ Hair dryer; ⁃ Fresh towels. Please note that the apartment faces the street in Raval quarter and it is very close to Las Ramblas. It is a very lively street, day and night. The rooms have double glazed windows, so you can barely hear noise at night time.
house_rules: My apartment has 2 rooms for guests that accommodate up to 4 people. The base price is for one of either room. The 3rd and 4th guest have an additional charge, this is automatically reflected when you chose the number of guests in your reservation. You can book the 2 rooms if you'd like just by selecting the number of guests to 3 otherwise you will be booking one room only, either the double bed with balcony or the double room with window. I share my home with my guests, this is not a full apartment reservation. Manuel arrived at our pre-arranged time to give us the keys and explain a few details, such as how to operate the wifi. He was very welcoming and told us a bit about Barcelona. 
The apartment felt safe - there were 3 locked doors to get in. We enjoy walking and felt safe walking in this neighbourhood. There are many interesting places to visit within walking distance, such as the Eixample area, La Rambla, and the National Art Museum. However if you are not a walker, cabs are easy to hail - cabs with a green light indicate they are available for hire. 
The suite is represented accurately in the photos. The supply of linens and towels was ample. The apartment is near a busy road which generates traffic noise at night - this may disturb light sleepers. Our first night was a Saturday night which might be a noisier night or we may have been suffering from jet-lag, but our sleep was disrupted. The rest of the week I slept well.
The bathroom is an ensuite off the master bedroom. Because we are family we were okay with this arrangement, but some people may feel uncomfortable passing through a room with sleeping people to use the toilet in the night.
There are loads of nearby shops to pick up groceries and other supplies such as hand soap, dish detergent, and toilet paper. 
Overall, the apartment was clean and it suited our needs well. I would stay again if I visit Barcelona again. comments_traducidos:
["Manuel was really nice and helpful. The apartment was cozy, clean, and in a great location. It had everything we needed and there were supermarkets nearby. Our only problem was that the main bedroom didn't have curtains. Manuel tried to hang them up but never quite got it right. Other than that, everything was good. It was just a 15-minute walk from the Ramblas. It was also close to the national museum and a shopping mall. There were easy transport links nearby with a metro station right outside. A perfect place for a comfortable stay and exploring Barcelona. I would definitely stay here again.", "It's perfectly located, has everything you need, and is super clean! It was exactly as described in the listing. We (3 girls, 1 guy, ages 22-27, from Austria) had three awesome days at Manuel's place. The fact that it's a 15 minute walk to La Rambla is soon forgotten because the metro stops right outside! And we were able to buy the only things missing in the flat (toilet paper and dishwasher liquid) next door.", "Manuel was a great host, super flexible and easy to work with. The place was beautiful and looked exactly like the pictures, super clean and perfect for our trip (4 people). The neighborhood was really nice with tons of shops, markets, and bakeries. Not right in the middle of everything so it wasn't too loud or busy, but close enough to walk to most of the good sights. If you don't feel like walking, the metro is literally steps away from the apartment and gives you access to all of Barcelona in minutes. It was a really nice place that I would definitely go back to for my next visit.", 'Cozy host, super flexible! 
Great apartment, charming with its vaulted ceiling, typical elevator.
Super location with the metro station just 50 meters away.
Tons of shops nearby.

Important point: spotless cleanliness, soft blankets that smell like laundry!

We highly recommend this apartment.', 'We had a good time in the apartment. Everything looked just like the pictures.  Everything worked, it was clean. Even though the place is close to Gran Via, it was quiet enough for us to sleep at night/early morning. Manuel was a nice and helpful host. I would recommend this to all my friends.', "Manuel's been a great host. The apartment was awesome, and we were so glad we chose it for our Barcelona trip!", "We had a great time staying at Manuel's apartment. It's super well-located, right in the heart of Barcelona, close to Rocafort metro station (line 1, which goes directly to Plaza Cataluña).  It was perfect for exploring the city! The apartment was spotless and fully equipped (wifi, kitchen, bedrooms, etc.). Finally, Manuel welcomed us warmly and took care of everything during our stay in Barcelona. We highly recommend it for anyone who wants to spend a few days in Barcelona.", "The house is exactly like the pictures show, nicely decorated with high ceilings and exposed beams. It's really pretty and perfectly located, close to the metro and walking distance. The beds are comfy and the pillows are great. Manuel helped us out with everything and gave us good recommendations for restaurants and things to do in the city.", "We didn't get to meet Manuel, but he arranged for Ingrid to welcome us and show us the apartment. Ingrid was really helpful, friendly, and nice - she helped us with parking and went out of her way to help us settle in. She gave great customer service and was a pleasure to deal with. The apartment was just like the pictures, well located, and clean. We were super happy with our choice! 
Garry and family.", 'The apartment was pretty much like the pictures, but keep in mind the rooms aren't real rooms. It was one big room with some walls separating it, and there's a gap to the ceiling about a meter high. So no real privacy. And it's really noisy from the street (nobody mentioned that before). I used earplugs so it wasn't too bad. 

This was the first time (out of about 10 times renting on Airbnb) I didn't enjoy communicating with the host. Manuel wanted 35 euros (in cash) for late check-in. I think that's normal, but it should be in the house rules! Otherwise it's not nice. And Manuel was out of town (since the day after we arrived) and couldn't help us with the apartment (no soap or washing liquid). He just said "sorry, I'm out of town" at the end of the day. I think if the host is out of town, they should be able to arrange someone to help guests while they can't do it themselves.', "My sister, her daughter, and I stayed in a suite in Barcelona for one week in November. Manuel gave us the keys and explained how to use the wifi. He was really nice and told us about Barcelona.

The apartment felt safe with three locked doors. We liked walking and felt safe doing it in this neighborhood. There are lots of interesting places nearby, like Eixample, La Rambla, and the National Art Museum. If you don't walk much, cabs are easy to hail - if a cab has a green light, it's available for hire.

The photos show the apartment accurately. There was plenty of linens and towels. The apartment is near a busy road which makes some noise at night - this might bother light sleepers. Our first night was on Saturday, so maybe that's why we had trouble sleeping. But the rest of the week I slept well.

The bathroom is an ensuite off the master bedroom. Since it's family, we were okay with this arrangement, but some people might feel uncomfortable using the toilet in the middle of the night when someone else is sleeping. 

There are tons of shops nearby to get groceries and other supplies like hand soap, dish detergent, and toilet paper.

Overall, the apartment was clean and it fit our needs well. I would stay there again if I go back to Barcelona.", "We've really enjoyed the apartment. The perfect neighborhood, close to my family and right next to a subway entrance made for a perfect stay. The flat is exactly as it looks in the pictures but it's actually pretty dark.", "At check-in, a girl was there waiting for us right on time at the entrance of the building. Our stay was comfy, the flat is super easy to get around since the tube station is right under it. The place was clean and fully stocked so we didn't have any issues. There's a garage for parking our car just 5 minutes away, which was convenient.  The location is central, so it can be a bit noisy because it's on one of the main streets leading to downtown. Around the corner there's a cool coffee shop called 'Fish and Chips' where you can get a great breakfast. Overall, it was a nice stay!", 'The house is super comfortable, just like the website said and in a great location with easy access to everything. Manuel was really helpful and nice to us. This place has been an awesome choice!', "Hey! Welcome from Lucia with some tips about the city, tapas places, etc. The house is super clean and well-equipped, but the best thing is the transport - it's right next to the metro, bus stop for the airport is just a 100m away, and there's another bus stop nearby too!  The neighborhood is pretty fancy with some new tapas places - I recommend Lolita (really good) and Tickets (but we haven't tried because there's a 2-month waiting list...). There might be some traffic noise and not super bright, but it doesn't bother me for a great stay in Barcelona.", "Manuel met me at this awesome place and he was really nice. It's super clean, everything you need is there. I'd recommend staying here if you're thinking about it. The location is perfect in Barcelona - right next to the metro station! This was the perfect birthday gift for my parents, and I would definitely stay here again.", "The apartment is clean but lacks some basic equipment. (No dishcloth for the kitchen, the oven is dirty, you have to do dishes before using it, some lightbulbs are burnt out, the apartment is above collective trash cans, be careful of mosquitos if you open the window... a plug in the main bedroom doesn't hold on the wall). 

Don't be surprised to pay the tourist tax upon arrival, this apartment is managed by an agency. 

Otherwise, it's very well located, there's a metro stop 10m from the building entrance, a underground parking lot nearby with advantageous prices for several nights (3 days => 30 euros)", "This place is awesome! It's super close to the metro and Plaza España, plus it's a nice walk to La Rambla and other tourist spots. The house has everything you need for a short or long stay, and Lucia was really welcoming!  Definitely recommend it!", "A different woman showed me around the place instead of the host. There was some city noise at night, but I managed to sleep well because it was tiring. The house is smaller than I thought, but it wasn't a problem for me since there were enough things.  The washing machine had a dryer function which was convenient. It was close to the metro station and easy to get around. There were lots of restaurants nearby, so it was convenient. Overall, it was a good place to stay.", "The description is mostly right. The location, off the Gran Via, is fine but the building isn't as well kept as other places on the Gran Via. The air conditioner never worked and just blew air around. It kind of reminds me of a stay hotel. This is a managed property, not a private owner one. Check-in was easy and the internet was about 8.5 MBps which was more than enough. The second bed is tiny - just be aware, I used it as a closet for my stuff. The metro is close and there are plenty of cabs on the Gran Via. It's adequate but not somewhere I would hang out. The management company was good to deal with.", "The apartment was awesome.  Manuel's helpers were super nice and helpful. Great location right next to the subway.", "The apartment gave us space and comfort (for four friends), the beds were comfy, the living area nice, good kitchen, and good proportions. 

The only problem we had was with the WiFi; it seemed to work sometimes which was annoying for short periods, besides that, great experience! It's 20 meters from the metro station and still super quiet, we slept with the windows open and it was perfect. 

Thanks Manuel for making our trip to Barcelona awesome!", 'Everything went great, top to bottom!', 'We had a good time at the apartment. Everything was okay. The metro is right next door.', "Great location. Comfortable apartment. Manuel and his helper organized the meeting perfectly. Overall, we're very happy with it. There was one small problem - for 4 people, there wasn't enough hot water to wash dishes in the evening. We had to take a shower first, then wash the dishes.", "The place is super convenient, right next to the metro and a short walk from Plaza España. It's big and comfy, pretty quiet too. Wifi, there's a microwave, toaster, and washing machine in the kitchen... 
Manuel will give you a warm welcome and be available for anything you need.", "Everything's great. The apartment is in excellent condition, just as described. The location is perfect.", "Everything was fine with the apartment. 
Just think it would be good if Manoel clarified that check-out isn't always flexible.  In fact, this was an important criterion for choosing the place since my mom, who is over 70 years old, needed it because her flight left at night (unlike me).
Other than that, no complaints. Clean, well-located and interesting apartment.
Thanks to Manoel!!", 'Easy check-in and check-out. Central location; clean, modern, and in good condition. Parking is very cheap right next door.', "My family and I really liked Manuel's place - his agent was nice and helpful, and it was good enough for our needs (just my wife, me, and our two adult daughters). There was plenty of space for all of us, and the neighborhood was chill and safe.  I recommend!", "This place was awesome! It was right next to the metro station, so exploring was super easy. Plus, it was on the second floor, so we didn't have to climb too many stairs. summary: Live during your vacations in the center of the most cosmopolitan neighborhood of the city of Barcelona. The comfortable room is ideal for short stays in the city. Having a sofa bed, allows you to have a space to be, a desk to work or connect to the Internet and quickly transform the room into a bedroom for two people. Go on public transport and take a walk through the little streets of the neighborhood, with its unique markets, bars and shops.
space: The house where the room is located is a house of the early twentieth century. It has the structure of the characteristic houses of the neighborhood of Gràcia: three stories high, on the ground floor, where the room is located, a family lives and in the upper two there is another family. The house has a spacious living room with modernist ceramics on its walls and a patio that accesses the main room of the house where its owners stay (this area is not accessible to guests, but its owners like to teach it, sometimes). The house is located at street level and is quiet and comfortable.

name: 2714 - AB Girona Apartment 41 - Stylish Apartment for up to 7 guests in Eixample with a Balcony
summary: Situated just 600 metres from the famous Passeig de Gràcia, this luxury apartment offers a balcony and air conditioning. It is located just 70 metres from Girona metro station.  The apartment sleeps up to 7 people across two double bedrooms, a single bedroom and a double sofa-bed. neighborhood_overview: La Barceloneta es un barrio marinero del distrito de Ciutat Vella de Barcelona.Actualmente, el barrio sigue teniendo ese aire de pueblo ajeno a la ciudad que siempre le ha caracterizado. Pero el ambiente ha cambiado mucho, sobre todo, en verano. Su playa es una de las más animadas de la ciudad tanto de día como de noche, cuando abren los chiringuitos y bares musicales instalados en la misma arena donde se puede ir a cenar o a tomar una copa hasta altas horas de la madrugada.Junto a esta cara moderna, la Barceloneta sigue oliendo a sal y a ambiente marinero. Para muchos es todo un lujo que todavía se conserve un barrio de este tipo en una ciudad como Barcelona. Y es que resulta algo extraño que junto a calles estrechas, húmedas y ennegrecidas por el salitre, convivan alguno de los mejores restaurantes de la ciudad y atraquen lujosos barcos.
notes: Se recomienda comprar agua envasada (evitar beber agua del grifo), se dispone de jarra con filtro para el agua
transit: Estacion de metro Barceloneta linea amarilla a 5 minutos caminando, autobus parada playa Barceloneta Nº 59,45,D20, caminando se puede llegar a los barrios de alrededor como el Born,Gotico,Rabal, Plaza Cataluñia. Existe parking a los alrededores del edificio. Desde el aeropuerto se puede acceder en renfe (tren) hacia estacion Sants con transbordo a estacion francia (6 estaciones en total , aprox 30 minutos,) y luego caminar 10 minutos o tomar autobus D20,59,45 parada Barceloneta y luego caminar 1 cuadra hacia el piso, tambien en taxi o en aerobus que los deja en plaza catalunya y luego autobus 59 (tomar en la rambla de catalunya) o metro linea amarilla (tomar en plaza urquinaona) bajarse en parada barceloneta y caminar 8 minutos al piso

Karla was very responsive over text and email, and I think she even shifted her plans around a bit so that she could meet me when I arrived in town rather than having me wait with my bags. She's a kind host. There are also a couple of pets--a Chihuahua and a shy, skittish cat--but they stayed mostly in her room.

The room is small and most of the space is occupied by the bed, which was comfortable and clean. There's a small area to hang up clothes as well. Other than that there wasn't much room in the room, but as I mentioned before there's a common area and a little balcony, so the small room isn't a problem. The kitchen and bathrooms were clean throughout my stay.

The apartment is located right by the beach, maybe a minute or two to walk there, and a short walk from the subway station (5 minutes). There are no shortage of bars and restaurants around the apartment, and Karla was able to suggest where to go. The neighborhood is safe and offers everything you need from a large grocery store, to a mercado, to corner stores, to restaurants and bars. comments_traducidos:
["Location is awesome! Tons of cool coffee shops, restaurants, and bars are nearby. You can walk to the beach in 3 minutes, and the metro and Barri Gotic are just a 10-minute stroll away.

The bed is huge (queen size at least) and has a really comfy mattress. I'm super sensitive to mattresses, so this was a big plus! The room isn't huge, but you won't spend much time in it.

The bathroom is okay - just enough for a quick shower. 

Karla is a great person, but she doesn't speak much English.  She'll learn and you can practice Spanish!", "Karla was really helpful even though I only speak English pretty well and she didn't speak much English. She kept the house clean and the common area looked nice, the balcony too. Karla was quick to respond via text and email and I think she even changed her plans a bit so she could meet me when I got there instead of having me wait with my luggage. She's a really nice host. There are also a couple of pets - a Chihuahua and a shy cat - but they mostly stayed in her room. 

The room is small, most of the space is taken up by the bed which was comfy and clean. There's a little area to hang clothes too. Other than that there wasn't much room in the room, but as I mentioned before there's a common area and a little balcony so the small room isn't a problem. The kitchen and bathrooms were always clean during my stay. 

The apartment is right by the beach, maybe a minute or two to walk there, and a short walk from the subway station (5 minutes). There are tons of bars and restaurants around the apartment, and Karla was able to suggest places to go. It's a busy part of town during the day and evening, but I didn't find it too loud at night. I recommend staying here if it's available.", "Karla's a fantastic person and an awesome host. She's a PhD student and was gone most of the day during the workweek. Her pets are cool too. They stayed to themselves while she was gone and came alive when she got back.

The Airbnb room is big with a huge bed and lots of outlets. The apartment itself is a two-bedroom place with a kitchen and living area. The toilet is separate from the shower. The views and breeze are great. You can see the beach, and Karla keeps the whole place super clean.

The neighborhood is safe and has everything you need - a big grocery store, a market, corner stores, restaurants, and bars. I liked being able to easily get to the beach anytime. The apartment's also close to major attractions. It only took me 15 minutes to walk to La Rambla, and 30 minutes to walk to La Sagrada Familia. If you don't like walking, the metro is just a short walk away, and the bus is nearby too.

Overall, it was a great way to experience the beach and Barcelona from a local's perspective. I had a great stay and would definitely recommend the apartment room and Karla as a host.", "Karla's was super welcoming! The room is tiny and basic, you have everything you need for a quick trip, even a balcony with a view of the beach. I'd definitely stay there again anytime I'm in Barcelona.", "Karla has a cozy little place in a great spot - right by the beach! She's super friendly and easy to hang out with. But I would definitely recommend this place for people traveling without kids!", "The place was super clean, right next to the beach, just a two-minute walk. Karla was really helpful and nice.", "Karla was super nice and welcoming, and I had a good time meeting her. Her English isn't perfect, but it's way better than my Spanish, and you can always figure out how to communicate. name: Modernist flat close to the Sagrada Familia
summary: Ideal for enjoying Barcelona with friends, family or even for business! This apartment is in compliance with the law being professionally managed by our family business ES-FLATS (Aurélie & Eberhard), we check the flat before and after each stay and manage cleaning and maintenance with a professional team. We have all the official licenses and insurances required to exercise the touristic rental, which is mandatory in Catalunya.
space: This nice bright apartment is located in the modernist district "Eixample "  near the most famous building of Antonio Gaudi: the Sagrada Familia and 5 minutes walking from Paseo Sant Joan and 15 min. from Paseo de Gracia, well known for his luxury stores. Located in a residential building, the apartment consists of two large bedrooms with double beds, one extra bed room with a sofa bed, a bathroom with shower and WC, a separate WC, a kitchen and a bright living room faced to the typical courtyard of Eixample, with a balcony along the flat. It is in the 2d floor with lift. We keep trying to be as much as possible “eco friendly”, so please help us to take care of the environment.

notes: Since the 1st of April 2017 the city tax rate is: 2,50EUR / person / night, we kindly ask you to prepare the corresponding amount in cash, to give at the check in. PS: This tax is applicable to the persons older than 17 years and only for the 7th first nights. Corporate social responsibility:  One part of our profit is donated to Doctors Without Borders and Help Children (Aldees Infantils SOS)

interaction: We offer to our guests an individual and personalised service, starting from the upstream communication, the arrival onsite and during the stay, until the departure.  We reply to all your questions in few hours and always do our best to fulfil your needs. After booking, you will receive a list of extra services such as Airport pick up, fridge stocking, activities, entrance to monuments… and you will have the possibility to book it in advance in order to enjoy the maximum of your stay. For the ones who come by car, we have agreements with most of the parkings around offering you the best prices to let your car in a safe place. We speak fluently 4 languages, English, French, German and Spanish, which is a big advantage to communicate and exchange information. We welcome our guests personally upon arrival; we give them information about the surrounding, some advices and a map of the city and the public transportation. We adapt the check-in to your arrival time when it is possible; note th
house_rules: Smoking allowed on balcony only.  When you leave the flat please always check that the air condition and lights are switched off and that the doors and windows are closed. Open window means no air condition switched on ;-) Because we respect our neighbors, no parties are allowed and we expect a responsible behavior especially on arrival and departure, lift use, staircase and public areas. Just the reserved number of people is allowed to sleep in flat.

Magui a été ponctuelle et très aimable.

'}, {'_id': '12853097', 'date': '2014-05-12T04:00:00Z', 'listing_id': '2843976', 'reviewer_id': '14710542', 'reviewer_name': 'Agnès', 'comments': "Une arrivée un peu tardive, mais nous étions attendus. Karen a été parfaite et d'une grande patience avec ses explications. Le logement correspond bien aux photographies, avec une petite odeur de peinture en plus... il vient d'être refait et c'est parfait. 
Avant d'aller dîner dans le quartier gothique, un verre de vin rouge car les courses commandées étaient livrées... et une bonne douche bien chaude... encore parfait.
Dans les chambres, des lits confortables, une literie neuve. Rien à dire que ce n'est que la couette de ma chambre a du disparaître avant notre arrivée. Mais il faisait chaud.
Quand à l'aménagement de la cuisine, il manque un peu de petite vaisselle (des bols pour manger les céréales du matin...) et quelques bricoles toutes simples (quelques pastilles pour la lave vaisselle, un peu de sel et de poivre, du vinaigre  - 
Tout cela n'a pas grande importance.
Tout y était.
Nous étions 4 - et c'était parfait.
L'emplacement est central.
L'appartement au second étage - avec ascenseur - donne sur l'arrière avec un petit balcon. Pas de bruit la nuit, nous avons peu laisser les portes fenêtres ouvertes.
La couleur blanche des murs se marrie bien avec les gris des faïences murales.
Les plafonds sont magnifiques.
L'aménagement du salon, dans sa simplicité est confortable et convivial. Il donne sur un petit balcon ou il fait bon prendre l'air.
Merci pour avoir contribué à rendre notre séjour à Barcelone agréable avec un havre de  repos bien mérité après des journées bien remplies.
Si vous aimez la netteté, la simplicité de très bon goût, je vous recommande cet appartement.

Firstly Barcelona is a great city for tourists. This particular area has a number of good restaurants and any number of cafes and shops including excellent bakeries. Think friendly Parisian restaurants and boulangeries and that about sums it up. 
Secondly the apartment is close to a few must see architectural goodies and two useful underground lines. 
Thirdly residents in the apartment block are friendly and courteous, though so was everyone in Barcelona.

comments_traducidos:
['The apartment is just like the pictures, in a quiet neighborhood close to all the tourist spots (Sagrada Familia, Ramblas, etc...). The metro station is a 5-minute walk away. 
Magui was punctual and very nice.
Recommend this place!', "A little late arrival, but we were expected. Karen was perfect and very patient with her explanations. The place matched the photos, with a slight paint smell in addition... it's just been redone and perfect. 
Before going to dinner in the gothic quarter, a glass of red wine because the groceries ordered were delivered... and a nice hot shower... still perfect.
In the bedrooms, comfortable beds, new bedding. Nothing to say except that my room's duvet disappeared before our arrival. But it was hot.
As for the kitchen setup, there's a little lack of small dishes (bowls for eating cereal in the morning...) and some simple trinkets (a few dishwasher tablets, a bit of salt and pepper, vinegar...). 
All this isn't that important.
Everything was there.
We were 4 - and it was perfect.
The location is central.
The second-floor apartment with an elevator overlooks the back with a small balcony. No noise at night, we kept the doors open a little.
The white walls match well with the gray of the wall tiles.
The ceilings are beautiful.
The living room setup, in its simplicity, is comfortable and convivial. It looks out onto a small balcony where you can enjoy fresh air. 
Thank you for helping make our stay in Barcelona enjoyable with a well-deserved break after busy days.
If you like neatness, the simple elegance of very good taste, I recommend this apartment.", "Everything was good at the apartment except the host wasn't there until an hour after check-in.  The place was awesome, it had all the stuff you need, and it was in a decent spot - close to the metro stations.", 'We loved staying here! The location is awesome - right next to the subway, a quick 25-minute ride to the Gothic Quarter, and just 10 minutes to Sagrada Familia. The apartment itself is brand new with a cool design and all the stuff you need. Eberhard and Aurelie are super helpful and friendly hosts.', "We had a good week in Barcelona. Talking to the host was a breeze. Totally recommend it!', 'We loved staying here! The apartment is gorgeous, super clean and comfy with everything you need.  The airport transfers were a huge help, made our trip so easy. Plus, they answered all our questions quickly. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking for a perfect stay in Barcelona!', "A killer place right in the heart of the city. It was super modern, spotless, and exactly what we wanted. The local guy, Magui, was a huge help. We'd totally recommend it!", 'This was our first time using Airbnb and it was amazing!  The communication was awesome, they made us feel taken care of. The place was great, the location was perfect, and checking in early was a huge help. We loved the space - it was so beautiful and well-lit. It felt safe and secure, and we could easily walk to everything we needed. It was like our home away from home!', "Great place, right in the heart of the city. Big enough for five of us to stay over a long weekend. Check-in and check-out were super easy, and the apartment matched the pictures perfectly. I'd definitely recommend it!", 'Great spot, friendly people. Taxi ride was only about €10 to get to the harbor.', 'Our trip was awesome, exactly what we hoped for. The host is super friendly and gets back to us fast. The apartment is gorgeous and in a great spot.', "Eberhard and Aurelie's place was awesome.  Amazing location, super quiet, big, comfy.  Perfect for exploring Barcelona!", "This is a cool old apartment building in a real neighborhood. It has a skinny elevator, narrow stairs, and it's dripping with character. Scenes from movies could happen anywhere inside. It was exactly what we were looking for.

The apartment looks out on the inside of the block, not to the street. It's quiet but there are no distant views. 

The people you see on the street live there. The shops and restaurants nearby are real neighborhood places. When you go in and out, when you walk around the area, you're getting a taste of how people live in big cities. 

Transportation is everywhere and there are tons of famous things within walking distance. We had a great walk to the harbor, stumbled upon two of the three train stations, and of course that big famous church is right up the street.  Walk ten blocks in any direction and you'll be surprised by all the cool stuff.", 'This is a great place to stay! The location is awesome, and the host was super helpful. I would definitely recommend it.', "This flat was in a great spot and super clean. The only problem was there wasn't any AC the whole time, and it was around 26-28 degrees in the loft all the time. We couldn't open the windows because of the construction noise on the main floor. Other than that, it was a good deal and a great location.", 'Great host, super nice! Thanks for the stay!', "Ever and Aurelia are awesome hosts! They answered our questions right away and gave us tons of helpful info. The apartment's location is great - just a 9-minute walk from Sagrada Familia. We can also easily walk to La Rambla and the Cathedral. There are supermarkets, shops, and restaurants nearby too. The apartment is super clean, and the kitchen has everything we need. We'll definitely stay here again if we come back to Barcelona!", 'Our stay was awesome. Everything was exactly as described. We felt right at home in the apartment.

The great location helped us get everywhere easily and quickly.

Definitely recommend it!', 'Nice place, awesome location, everything we needed! Check-in was super easy and we booked a transfer from the airport with Airbnb, which was great. Easy to get around everywhere from the flat, either by public transport or walking, and some really good restaurants right near the flat.', 'A cool place to live in a good spot.', "This apartment was awesome! It had great lighting, it was super quiet, and the beds were comfy. It was a perfect size for us four, and we could have easily had another person stay over without feeling cramped. The location was awesome too. We were close to the metro stops and went to the bakery/cafe across the street every morning (Teixidó). 

We were warmly welcomed and although we never needed to contact Aurélie & Eberhard, we knew they would be responsive. 

We'd love to stay there again next time we're in Barcelona.", "This place is super clean and huge! There was tons of space for my mom, me, and my daughter to chill out. It's right next to Sagrada Familia and there are so many awesome restaurants within walking distance. I'd totally come back here!", 'Nice place near Sagrada and the metro', "We loved our time in Barcelona! The apartment was super comfy and in a great spot, so we could walk to most places we wanted to go. Unfortunately, there was an electricity issue the whole time we were there that made the power go out whenever we tried to use even just a few appliances.  The hosts say this problem is fixed now, so it shouldn't be an issue for future guests.", "Cool apartment that was way bigger than I thought. Check-in was super easy and the place was spotless. Thanks for letting us stay last minute!", 'I loved it! The location and decor were awesome, would totally recommend.', "We really liked how easy it was to communicate and check in late! It's awesome for people flying in at night who want somewhere to chill out before their flight in the morning.  Great spot, we'll definitely book again!", "Awesome flat with three bedrooms. The owners were super nice and helpful the whole time. I'd totally recommend staying here!"]

Paral.lel is an avenue that cuts down from picturesque Plaça Espanya right down to the World Trade Centre at the tip of the port. Poble Sec is an area spreading out from the middle of Paral.lel. The areas are safe and primarily residential but there is much entertainment to be had as well. This includes popular bars, theatre and even a club. However, whilst Paral.lel is a busy thoroughfare during the day, the areas are quiet and just a 10-20 minute walk to the centre of the city and Las Ramblas. A new meeting place in Barcelona. Ciutat Vella is one of the most lively and varied districts in Barcelona. The serenity of its hidden corners, dark and narrow streets, and almost haunted squares breathe life and diversity. In Ciutat Vella you can follow in the footsteps of ancient Romans, pray in Gothic churches reaching for the sky, stroll through the palaces built by the businessmen back from the colonies for their mistresses, follow the trail of the great Modernista architects and enjoy the most contemporary cultural offering in the city in the El Raval neighbourhood.

From here you can get to Passeig de Gràcia, Diagonal, Poble Sec, Palau Reial. From here, you can also go to Sants Estació and, from here, you can get the train that will take you directly to the airport.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in Gracia, which is a charming and elegant neighbourhood in the center of Barcelona. You will enjoy the best of catalonia’s modernism by walking through its streets, shops and cafés and get astonished by Gaudí’s most beautiful works such as Casa Milá or Casa Batlló, iconic pieces of this genius architecture. You will be only one block away from the famous Hospital Sant Pau, also a masterpiece from Gaudi, with its astonishing exposed-bricks construction and the charming Paseo Gaudí, one the most beautiful streets in Barcelona to enjoy walking, as no cars are allowed and plenty of shops, bars and restaurants offer the best of the local food throughout many terraces. Verdi street is also one of the most popular streets and is very close by, you can also make a special time to pay a visit it.  You will be located in an centric well connected area, with the city’s finest restaurants.
notes: You will be required to present your ID/Passport upon arrival. In order to follow local regulations and to be able to register all our guests on the local police’s database, we will have to take pictures of ID documents for all guests. I hope this is not an inconvenient!
transit: You couldn't be at a most fine location! Sant Pau (L5 blue line) is the nearest station to the apartment, just a doorstep away. Literally, you will only need to step out the door and you will face the tube station! This connects you to the blue line, meaning you can get to iconic Barcelona sites in no time at all, such as the Basilica of Sagrada Familia (15 minutes away) or even the beach, which is only 20 minutes away. There are also plenty of buses around the apartment such as the V21, that stops just two blocks away and that will take you all over the city with the best connections. Try the paella or the super hot patatas bravas in the amazing Restaurante Azul or enjoy some spicy and exotic delicatessen at Restaurante Peruano Andino, only two blocks away down Av. Gaudí.  You will enjoy this neighborhood very much, we are happy to welcome you to it! name: Sunny Attic with Pool and Terrace near the Beach!
summary: Beautiful and sunny high standing Attic/Penthouse with large roof terrace and community pool and garden.
space: In the heart of trendy Poblenou area and a few minutes walking distance from Mar Bella Beach. If you look for the mix of cool urban living and relaxed beach and park life...this is your place! The neighborhood is characterised by the thrilling contrast of old Mediterranean building structures, refurbished lofts and stunning new architecture by international stars as Jean Nouvel, Domenique Perault and Carlos Ferrater. The flat has plenty of light, a large roof terrace for sun bathing, on the ground floor a big garden with a children area and a swimming pool to cool off after a day of shopping or sight seeing. The subway stop is right next door and brings you in 10 minutes to all major sights. The beach with its vibrant club and restaurant scene can easily be reached by foot.
